0.1.1

* bugfix: encoding options was "optional" but omitting them raised a TypeError
* bugfix: exception when handling empty DBF tables
* bugfix: :target option was being ignored


0.1.0

* for now, only supporting DBF files as origin
* encoding conversion (supporting many encodings for the same table)
* deleted records in DBF tables are ignored
* handles name conflicts between field names and SQL reserved words/core Ruby methods
* allows definition of a different type for a field when creating the target table

